cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and neural networks, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the integration of traditional algorithms into neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses BiLSTM, which is a type of recurrent neural network, and thus could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
